    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In design, the positioning of two elements set facing each other, such as two mirror-image figures facing toward each other. Examples are in heraldry and architectural ornament. For two figures set back-to-back, use "addorsed."</Note_Text>
